### Current Behavior

I am building an Angular Nx application and I wish to print out a message to the console to help me debug a cypress test. I am trying to use my fixture data and verify that the data is loading:

```
before(function () {
    cy.fixture('project.json').then(function (json) {
        data = json;
        cy.task('log', {message: 'This will be output to the terminal'})
    });
});
```
When I run ` nx component-test mylib` I get the following error: 
`CypressError: `cy.task('log')` failed with the following error:
The 'task' event has not been registered in the setupNodeEvents method. You must register it before using cy.task()
Fix this in your setupNodeEvents method here:
C:\Work\Master\myproj\libs\mylib\cypress.config.ts
https://on.cypress.io/api/task`

Here is what my full 
Because this error occurred during a `before all` hook we are skipping all of the remaining tests.

