### Additional Information

I traced the issue down to the `getPackageMigrationsConfigFromRegistry` function within https://github.com/nrwl/nx/blob/15.9.x/packages/nx/src/command-line/migrate.ts. This function attempts to retrieve migration metadata, from the registry, using `npm view <package name>@<version> nx-migrations ng-update --json`. Unfortunately, according to the GitLab documentation (https://docs.gitlab.com/ee/user/packages/npm_registry/#npm-metadata) it only supports [abbreviated metadata format](https://github.com/npm/registry/blob/9e368cf6aaca608da5b2c378c0d53f475298b916/docs/responses/package-metadata.md#abbreviated-metadata-format). As result the requested fields aren't returned and the migrate command thinks that the plugin has no migrations defined. 

A potential way of fixing this would be to also retrieve the `dist` field. In the event that the migration metadata fields aren't returned then the registry, within `dist.tarball`, could be compared against a whitelist of registries that are known to support the full metadata format. If a match is not found then an error could be thrown, which would cause `fetchMigrations` to fall through to the catch block and fall back to using `getPackageMigrationsUsingInstall` to determine the migrations.

### Current Behavior

the file template for jest.config.ts (`https://github.com/nrwl/nx/blob/master/packages/jest/src/generators/jest-project/files-angular/jest.config.ts__tmpl__`) contains the old syntax for ts-jest options. With the addition of Jest 29 support, there is currently a migration for existing files, but the generator will continue to create old versions even for updated repos.

### Expected Behavior

jest 29 support should be detected, and the appropriate jest.config values should be used.

