## Current Behavior

The `node:webpack` executor always [resolves the root tsConfig file](https://github.com/nrwl/nx/blob/b35e3836c2f3d45decbeb071efd26f54923e802b/packages/node/src/executors/webpack/webpack.impl.ts#L48-L50) and not the value specified in the options (like [`web:webpack` does](https://github.com/nrwl/nx/blob/b35e3836c2f3d45decbeb071efd26f54923e802b/packages/web/src/executors/webpack/webpack.impl.ts#L93-L96)). My app tsConfig file has compiler option `module: "commonjs"` while the root has `module: "esnext"`. 

If I provide a custom webpack config with the `webpackConfig` option set to a `.ts` file, the build fails with error `Cannot use import statement outside a module`. The error comes from trying to parse the custom `webpackConfig` file.

## Expected Behavior

The executor should respect the provided tsConfig option and default to the root tsConfig otherwise.

